list.abstract: 《Born》是Philip Halloun作词、作曲，常思思演唱的一首歌曲，于2017年11月16日发行。

yingyinNormal.en: My mother was born before your first cities were built.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我妈妈出生时地球还一片荒芜。

yingyinNormal.en: I was born in Japan, at a military base in Okinawa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我出生在日本冲绳的军事基地。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, I weighted like 27 pounds when I was born so…
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，我出生时有27磅，所以…

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, yes, born alone, die alone. It's a tragic human condition.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当然了，孤单的出生，孤独的死去，人类就是如此悲剧。

yingyinNormal.en: I was their first born. They thought she was barren. It's not my fault.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没出生前，他们以为她不会生。那不是我的错。

yingyinNormal.en: How do you know? Because I know. I was born. You were made.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么知道？因为我就是知道，我是出生的，你是被制造出来的。

yingyinNormal.en: You see, he's the Prince. Apparently they had some big ceremony before I was born.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他是个王子，显然，他们在我出生前有个大型仪式。

yingyinNormal.en: Muggle? Non-magic folk. This boy's had his name down ever since you were born.
yingyinNormal.zh: 麻瓜？不懂魔法的人，这孩子自从你出生之前就注册了。

yingyinNormal.en: December 25, 1642, Julian calendar, Sir Isaac Newton is born. Jesus, on the other hand, was actually born in the summer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 公历1642年12月25日，艾萨克·牛顿爵士诞生，而另一方面，耶稣其实夏天出生的。

yingyinNormal.en: When he was born, did it ever occur to you to ask your captor to take Jack away?
yingyinNormal.zh: 他出生之后，你...你有没有想过让囚禁你的人把杰克送走？

yingyinNormal.en: Sons of Adam. Cain was the first man to be born. Abel, the first to die.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们是亚当的儿子，该隐是世上第一个出生的人，而亚伯却是第一个死的人。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean I, well I think I can figure it out. I guess you know I was born, and everyone started lying their asses off.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我猜想得到我出生之后，大家都开始撒谎了。

yingyinNormal.en: Come up here, daughter. Look how tall she is. She's been taller than me since the day she was born.
yingyinNormal.zh: 过来，闺女，看她多高，从她出生那天起她就比我高了。

yingyinNormal.en: You were born at midnight. I was Pharaoh, and I had seen wonders most men only dream of.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你出生在午夜。我是法老，我见过的奇观，多数人只在梦里见过。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb》

yingyinNormal.en: Sometimes, I think I'm cursed. 'Cause of something that happened before I was even born.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有时候，我觉得自己被诅咒了，这个诅咒源于我出生前发生的一些事。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, did she sound happy about it? Because my friend Ethel's baby was born with a teeny-tiny beard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她听起来口气高不高兴？我有个朋友的孩子刚出生就有点胡子。

yingyinNormal.en: Three are Saudis? Here legally on F-1 student visas. Yasin Said was born in Michigan.
yingyinNormal.zh: 三名沙特人？他们持F1学生签证合法入境，亚辛·赛义德出生在密歇根州。

yingyinNormal.en: Pammy? Oh, yes. Listen, Nick, when she was born, Tom was God knows where, with God knows whom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你说帕米？是的。尼克，她出生的时候天知道汤姆在哪和谁鬼混在一起。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, so we get born. We learn to walk and talk. We meet our friends. Then what? You know.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很好，我们出生了。然后学会了走路和说话。遇见了朋友，然后呢？你懂的。

yingyinNormal.en: Uncle's most precious, born in the Year of the Monkey. That's why you're so clever, precious and clever.
yingyinNormal.zh: 舅舅最珍贵的小宝贝，猴年出生，所以你才如此聪慧，珍贵且聪慧。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: to come out of your mother's body at the beginning of your life; (of an idea, an organization, a feeling, etc.) to start to exist
sense_info_list.zh: 出生; 出现; 形成

examination_example.sentence: It was with these great revelations that a new kind of philosophy founded in reason was <highlight>born</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正是有了这些伟大的启示，一种建立在理性基础上的新哲学诞生了。

examination_example.sentence: Today's farm laborers, while still predominantly <highlight>born</highlight> in Mexico, are more likely to be settled rather than migrating.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当今的农场工人，虽然仍主要在墨西哥出生，但更有可能定居而不是迁移。

examination_example.sentence: Dickens was <highlight>born</highlight> in Portsmouth, on England's southern coast.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 狄更斯出生于英格兰南部海岸的Portsmouth。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们天生就有更强的社交能力。

examination_example.sentence: Robert Goddard, an American <highlight>born</highlight> in 1882, is widely regarded as the world's first rocket scientist.

examination_example.sentence: A child <highlight>born</highlight> into a low-income family in San Jose had a 12.9 percent chance of becoming a high earner as an adult.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个出生在圣何塞低收入家庭的孩子成年后成为高收入者的几率为12.9%。

examination_example.sentence: The Chetty data shows that neighborhoods and places mattered for children <highlight>born</highlight> in the San Jose area of 1980s.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 切蒂的数据显示，20世纪80年代出生在圣何塞地区的儿童所处的社区和地点至关重要。

examination_example.sentence: Service stations came with the motorway and the legend of the transport cafe was <highlight>born</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 服务站随高速公路而来，交通咖啡馆的传奇由此诞生。

examination_example.sentence: Children are <highlight>born</highlight> builders, makers, and creators, so fostering (培养) 21st-century skills may be simple.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子生来就是建筑师、制造者和创造者，所以培养21世纪的技能可能很简单。

examination_example.sentence: We are not <highlight>born</highlight> to handle quantitative distinctions skillfully.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们不是生来就能熟练地处理数量差异。

examination_example.sentence: The city has long had a large foreign-<highlight>born</highlight> population, leading to broader diversity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这座城市长期以来拥有大量的外国出生人口，导致了更广泛的多样性。

examination_example.sentence: This is a city of immigrants—38 percent of the city's population today is foreign-<highlight>born</highlight>—and immigrants have historically experienced significant upward mobility in America.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是一座移民城市——今天，该城市38%的人口是在外国出生的，移民在美国历史上经历了显著的向上流动。

examination_example.sentence: When the tiny creature arrived on January 31, she became the 40th black rhino to be <highlight>born</highlight> at the reserve.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当这只小动物于1月31日抵达时，她成为了保护区出生的第40只黑犀牛。

examination_example.sentence: Three of the four Lincoln sons were <highlight>born</highlight> here.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 林肯的四个儿子中有三个出生在这里。

examination_example.sentence: His mother, grandmother and great grandmother were all <highlight>born</highlight> at the reserve and still live there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的母亲、祖母和曾祖母都出生在保护区，现在仍然住在那里。

examination_example.sentence: What does Paul Beer say about the <highlight>new-born</highlight> rhino?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 保罗·比尔对新生的犀牛有什么看法？

examination_example.sentence: They had their first <highlight>born</highlight> in January.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们在一月份生了第一个孩子。

examination_example.sentence: I was a <highlight>born</highlight> performer who preferred the theatrical, even when off stage.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我是一个天生的演员，喜欢戏剧，即使是在舞台之外。
